definitions.definition: The state of being feminine ; femininity .
A social theory or political movement which argues that legal and social restrictions on women must be removed in order to bring about equality of the sexes in all aspects of public and private life.

main_definition: ( obsolete ) The state of being feminine ; femininity . [from 1851; less common after 1895]
secondary_definitions: A social theory or political movement which argues that legal and social restrictions on women must be removed in order to bring about equality of the sexes in all aspects of public and private life.
